"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-rail\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-eyebrow\">Popular right now</span><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Tap to jump to the full answer.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip-row\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-question-circle\"></i>Which Philadelphia neighborhoods have the best dog parks?</button></div></div><div role=\"list\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-accordion\"><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">01</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Which Philadelphia neighborhoods have the best dog parks?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Center City, Fairmount, and South Philadelphia all have excellent options.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">cities</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Center City, Fairmount, and South Philadelphia all have excellent options. The Schuylkill River Trail area features one of the city&#x27;s largest and most scenic dog parks.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->cities</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">02</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Can I take my dog hiking in the Poconos?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Yes!</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">Planning Your Visit</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Yes! Most Pocono state parks and forests welcome leashed dogs on trails. Some swimming and beach areas may have seasonal restrictions.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->Planning Your Visit</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article></div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"state-section alt\"><div class=\"section-shell\"><div class=\"cta-band\"><div><h3>Help us expand <!-- -->Pennsylvania<!-- --> coverage</h3><p>Submit your favorite spot and we’ll review it for inclusion in the directory.</p></div><div style=\"display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap\"><a class=\"hero-cta primary\" href=\"/list-your-park\"><i class=\"bi bi-plus-circle\"></i>List your park</a><a class=\"hero-cta ghost\" href